A LibreOffice-compatible sequential ranking formula is:

`=IF(Jr="","",SUMPRODUCT(($I$6:$I$607=Ir)*($B$6:$B$607>Br))+COUNTIFS($I$6:Ir,Ir,$B$6:Br,Br))`

This does:
- count rows in the same Item Class with larger Net Sales, then
- add the running count of equal Net Sales within that same class up to the current row,
so ties become 1,2,3… sequentially in row order.

